               <p>MR. SUTHERTON BACKLER. I am a student at Cambridge, and live at Thavies Inn. On the 29th of July, between one and two o'clock in the afternoon, I was walking on the right hand side of <placeName id="t18200918-110-crimeloc629">Fleet-market</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-110-crimeloc629" type="placeName" value="Fleet-market"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-110-crimeloc629" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-110-off627 t18200918-110-crimeloc629"></join>, and missed my handkerchief as I was going to use it. I turned round, and saw the prisoner close to me; I collared him, and saw his waistcoat protruded, lifted it up, and took my handkerchief from it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence, I saw two lads drop it, and I picked it up; it was not in my waistcoat, but in my hand.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200918-110-verdict630" type="verdictDescription">
